arChildNodes.szComment:
Everyone is violently thrown backwards as shockwaves burst through the room. 
Things become disorienting: sounds ringing, sight blurring, everything shaking. The room spins. 
The Player looks around disoriented and then horrified. 
The world is no longer the Vault of Light, but instead they are within the fleshy body cavity of Mephisto’s torso from the opening PRC. 
Massive lungs pulse and veins throb with blood, all leading to his horrific and titanic face looking down on them from a great height. 
When he speaks, the voice echoes, coming from all places and within the Player and Neyrelle’s mind. 
Neyrelle curls up, horrified recoiling from the attack on her mind and reliving the torment.

The voice snaps her out of the fugue, she looks around and sees Eru.  
Neyrelle is shouting something, but we can’t quite hear what she says.

As our senses clear, we finally see the hulking shape of the HARBINGER OF HATRED stalking 
towards the Player as Neyrelle’s words surface. The Lion lies prone under a pile of rubble.
Behind the Harbinger, the shape of Eru comes into focus.
He hesitates at the still-open tear, Akarat’s body tossed over his shoulder, the soulstone clutched in his free hand.

Eru turns his head to the Player for one heavy moment, pain and regret etched into his face. 
But he is too ashamed to hold their gaze.

He (Eru) slips into the tear and leaves. It closes with finality behind him. 
The Player gets back onto their feet, ready to fight.
The Harbinger of Hatred stalks toward the player.
The Harbinger bristles and growls as he approaches them, looming over their small form.
